.TH "ice_sched_set_node_bw" 9 "ice_sched_set_node_bw" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_sched_set_node_bw \- set node's bandwidth
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum ice_status" ice_sched_set_node_bw
.BI "(struct ice_port_info *pi "  ","
.BI "struct ice_sched_node *node "  ","
.BI "enum ice_rl_type rl_type "  ","
.BI "u32 bw "  ","
.BI "u8 layer_num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pi" 12
port information structure
.IP "node" 12
tree node
.IP "rl_type" 12
rate limit type min, max, or shared
.IP "bw" 12
bandwidth in Kbps - Kilo bits per sec
.IP "layer_num" 12
layer number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function adds new profile corresponding to requested BW, configures
node's RL profile ID of type CIR, EIR, or SRL, and removes old profile
ID from local database. The caller needs to hold scheduler lock.
